The paper deals with linear codes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The codes are constructed using algebraic techniques, which are also relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The codes may have applications in communication systems (cs.CC) and secret sharing schemes (cs.SI).
